# .cqmignore — Pattern file for CQM digest suppression
#
# Format: one pattern per line. Lines starting with # are comments.
# Patterns (see scripts/lib/cqm_status_detector.js for full grammar):
#   path/to/file.js          — exact file match (any line)
#   path/to/file.js:42       — exact file:line match
#   path/to/file.js:10-20    — line range (inclusive)
#   scripts/test_*.js        — glob (basic * support)
#
# Why these entries exist:
#   - Test files (scripts/test_*.js) are out-of-scope for CQM digest:
#     they're ephemeral, hand-written for specific phases, and not deployed.
#   - Skill scripts (skills-learned/*/scripts/) are owned by their skill
#     directory; CQM scans them but they shouldn't surface in main repo digest.

# === Test files (out-of-scope) ===
scripts/test_*.js

# === Skill scripts (owned by skill directories) ===
skills-learned/*/scripts/*.js

# === Benign magic numbers (intentional design decisions) ===
# 20480 = .session_handoff.md size cap (bytes). Truncates to prevent memory blowout.
scripts/cross_session_bootstrap.js:737
# 7000 = DeepSeek rate-limit backoff between LLM calls (ms). Intentionally tuned.
scripts/skill_reviewer_bot.js:2095

# === Rule definition files (comment-only simplified-chinese, not user-visible) ===
# The simplified-chinese.ast.js file is a rule DEFINITION; the "bug" it documents
# was in the OLD naive version. The AST-aware version intentionally uses
# simplified-chinese in explanatory comments only.
scripts/lib/rules/simplified-chinese.ast.js
